# AI Surface Layout (Mandatory)

All skills, agents, hooks, and Claude Code mirrors **must** follow project layout standards. `AGENTS.md` wins on policy; this rule wins on **structure**.

## Canonical standards

| Surface | Standard | Max entry size |
| ------- | -------- | -------------- |
| **Skills** | `.cursor/standards/agent-skills/STANDARD.md` + [agentskills.io](https://agentskills.io/home) | `SKILL.md` ≤ **80 lines** |
| **Agents** | `.cursor/standards/agent-layout/STANDARD.md` | entry `.md` ≤ **65 lines** |
| **Claude Code** | `.cursor/standards/claude-code/STANDARD.md` | lean `CLAUDE.md`; detail in `rules/` |
| **Hooks** | `.cursor/hooks.json` + `.cursor/hooks/` | one concern per hook script |
| **Knowledge base** | `.agents/knowledge/` (repowiki) + root `AGENTS.md` | entries lean; detail in subfolders |

## Required folder layout

### Skills (`.cursor/skills/<name>/`, `.qoder/skills/`, `.github/skills/`)

```
<skill-name>/
  SKILL.md          # YAML frontmatter: name, description (trigger terms)
  scripts/          # optional — subprocess helpers
  references/       # detailed docs — load on demand
  assets/           # templates, static outputs
```

### Agents (`.cursor/agents/`)

```
<agent-name>.md              # ENTRY — frontmatter + lean body (Cursor discovery)
<agent-name>/
  references/                # workflow, checklists, domain detail
  scripts/                   # optional
  assets/                    # REPORT-TEMPLATE.md etc.
```

**Never** nest entry files in subfolders — Cursor loads flat `.cursor/agents/<name>.md` only.

### Shared knowledge base (`.agents/knowledge/`)

```
.agents/knowledge/
  README.md          # read/write protocol (frontmatter, evidence, supersede-never-delete)
  index.md           # table of contents — update on every add
  architecture/  decisions/  patterns/   glossary.md
```

Single source of truth for cross-agent knowledge; tool paths `.claude/knowledge`,
`.cursor/knowledge`, `.qoder/repowiki` are symlinks to it (via `.claude/scripts/sync-surfaces.sh`).
Enforced by `pnpm ai check`.

## Authoring rules (every create/update)

1. **Progressive disclosure** — entry = mandate + workflow links; move tables, code samples, and long checklists to `references/`.
2. **Description is the router** — YAML `description` must include trigger terms and `Anti-trigger:` line.
3. **Gold contract** — every agent entry links `_shared/references/gold-standard-contract.md`.
4. **No policy fork** — never soften `AGENTS.md`; mirror only.
5. **Validate before done** — run `pnpm ai check` when touching AI surfaces.
6. **Import/path changes** — after agent edits that move files, run `import-auditor` or `pnpm type-check`.

## Subagent creation checklist

When using `/create-subagent` or adding `.cursor/agents/<name>.md`:

- [ ] `name` (kebab-case) + specific `description` with anti-triggers
- [ ] Entry ≤65 lines; detail in `<name>/references/`
- [ ] `assets/REPORT-TEMPLATE.md` if agent produces reports
- [ ] Update `.cursor/rules/04-subagent-auto-routing.mdc` inventory
- [ ] Update `.cursor/agents/README.md`
- [ ] Run `pnpm ai check`

## Skill creation checklist

- [ ] `SKILL.md` ≤80 lines; tables/long config → `references/`
- [ ] `description` names when to activate (include "MUST" / "use proactively" where appropriate)
- [ ] Scripts in `scripts/`; no inline bash blocks >10 lines in entry
- [ ] Run `pnpm ai check`

## Enforcement

`pnpm ai check` warns on oversized entries. Fix by moving content to `references/` — do not raise line limits.

Meta-skills: `agent-layout`, `skill-layout`, `claude-code-layout`.
